{"id": "4b0a92b630c0e744cd7177c85c1f0f03fefe220192f5724c778ad3a22594db69", "item_id": "681da43393:0", "text": "The Maya file node provides a convenient way to apply textures to surfaces and drive parameters. However, RenderMan only supports a subset of the controls based on the preferred workflow."}
{"id": "fe566a18ffe46a8a02a3e00c4e49cafd24b3b5ec29c10678046c6145749687a7", "item_id": "681da43393:1", "text": "Supported Features:"}
{"id": "f2b5e1669adc36f0fb6397b42f4b80dadf0597e454a62cf7dfaf0a62edd188ea", "item_id": "681da43393:2", "text": "File Attributes"}
{"id": "162e6cc0e295a973c8438c04f558cbb46315f49afabcfb6e665d0a5036d39637", "item_id": "681da43393:3", "text": "Image Name"}
{"id": "0186fe7a4727cd4774742e8741da2064ed97fbfe3a3a8d02c5fa1cf9f1018ebc", "item_id": "681da43393:4", "text": "- The path to the texture(s) you want to use"}
{"id": "a7bb98be7ad919691f5c4d22b98717b71a95a3246dc92abca25d1a55ec4990d0", "item_id": "681da43393:5", "text": "UV Tiling Mode"}
{"id": "36ed515bc06a97aee42659f5c72d41e486ef0d7b1beb0f3bbc01542ab2234a0c", "item_id": "681da43393:6", "text": "- We support all except for Explicit Tiles"}
{"id": "6ef03c4db0205fe815b37f7c7254623896390ba2bbc13552f5393fc70eb74461", "item_id": "681da43393:7", "text": "Use Image Sequence"}
{"id": "daea9abd606d4500d9ff7f6ad040a3d6029299aee6f164b0c96b3164b41a9d1d", "item_id": "681da43393:8", "text": "- This can be more convenient than using expressions in other nodes"}
{"id": "11af68c17c8f95b87abf4c80c2f29635070f4040cbbadca2beebadbaaa5327e8", "item_id": "681da43393:9", "text": "Color Balance"}
{"id": "b4012d9cfde926163a82046b882b5524c97ddc5b2d90a07b4ff1926eb9598fe4", "item_id": "681da43393:10", "text": "Default Color"}
{"id": "36795bc301312013812af959ed36278a29e244a9a6a3d133cbfece84aadacd59", "item_id": "681da43393:11", "text": "- This color fills-in where there is no texture coverage"}
{"id": "4f185221771c6d58fd2cad1903bf774fb0bcec3fed7dc0f511b70e10c758e3fe", "item_id": "681da43393:12", "text": "Color Gain"}
{"id": "aa798e0579410b05f512f41557b2012d16bb7772dd4dd9dc42542d4c03d936c9", "item_id": "681da43393:13", "text": "- This is a color multiplier for the texture"}
{"id": "c54f3e0aa08775c55e47d2cf166b9abf18efa1edd69d16a07effb5ef590201d4", "item_id": "681da43393:14", "text": "Color Offset"}
{"id": "bc4de54fa3c5b1d966746e433cdae9ffe5497ac59fd04a00dbd7d82d994080f4", "item_id": "681da43393:15", "text": "- Adds this color value to the texture"}
{"id": "c091f37dab29f348b7fa86e2ac5836c85a7dd5fa937c128e61ef6d3d72747d73", "item_id": "681da43393:16", "text": "Alpha Gain"}
{"id": "4361b2270a764db2113914c921620688ab2644ef1273363d44bfb6e07f809ce8", "item_id": "681da43393:17", "text": "- A multiplier for the texture alpha value (your texture needs an alpha channel unless you have selected Alpha is Luminance)"}
{"id": "04cf06a8826634b62fd84fbd9e63e4bd4537ec8591f7ad933f746068830e5454", "item_id": "681da43393:18", "text": "Alpha Offset"}
{"id": "8d04a656d61b3497f3f4201dad68e2b139e53a649b7a15336b2c5be57131c1a7", "item_id": "681da43393:19", "text": "- Adds this value to the alpha value of the texture (your texture needs an alpha channel unless you have selected Alpha is Luminance)"}
{"id": "358511c8c09805c9c10b1ba11157ed0c08ced8599d59e27e16fa226bdc32d63e", "item_id": "681da43393:20", "text": "Effects"}
{"id": "7e04f2ffb9334e3d19a15c949a73818d4b271b0e713dbfad612b29491b46bc1b", "item_id": "681da43393:21", "text": "Invert"}
{"id": "18a648c21d043073e4227a3166a25d40137238e235d9f3e5ddc1ca7eda2a9b4c", "item_id": "681da43393:22", "text": "- Inverts the values of the texture, colors become their opposite value on the color wheel"}
{"id": "8f75d9b72f10efd3ede2c86a408644698965a4ee60c7fb70b7933011bb4d6cbf", "item_id": "681da43393:23", "text": "Color Remap"}
{"id": "f46f1a97490ef5ee264db5c7adb854c04599ba0d8c5a86370d0bc36fc7bbdb01", "item_id": "681da43393:24", "text": "- Use a ramp to change hue and contrast values"}
{"id": "740863cb4a76bc5abe3e97f0e0a7cc6fce10a18bdd7382026d83aeefe9f2ee79", "item_id": "681da43393:25", "text": "RenderMan Controls:"}
{"id": "cd0c5ae6278f99edd8a70fa640c2bd321248f8c353202d1587c8b14f913379e4", "item_id": "681da43393:26", "text": "We use our own file filtering options contained in the RenderMan rollout. We recommend Box and it is the default."}
